  "original_title": "\u0bb5\u0bc6\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a \u0b8a\u0bb4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Notice to Govt servants going abroad",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Government servants who go abroad on unpaid leave are required to remit a specified amount to Sri Lanka every month.",
        "The circular also mentioned that the money should be sent to the foreign currency account in their name through the banking system in the country.",
        "Among the expatriate employees, primary level officials should remit US$ 100 and secondary officials should remit US$ 200.",
        "It is also indicated that it is mandatory for third level officials to send 300 US dollars and high level officials 500 US dollars to Sri Lanka."
      ],
